{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:40:59.179Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Optimizing MetricTile Layouts**\n\nI've been drilling into the `MetricTile` component, especially its mobile responsiveness. Switching the layout from a simple flex row to a more adaptive flex-col/flex-row setup with `sm:` breakpoints is key. Specifically, transitioning from `flex items-center justify-between` to `flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-4` is yielding more elegant results. This stacking approach on smaller screens ensures readability, even on the narrowest devices. Now I am considering responsive sparkline sizing.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:41:01.439Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Mobile Sparkline Handling**\n\nI'm focused on the layout changes of the sparkline chart and text, and ensuring it stacks correctly. I've re-examined the `components/private-app/cards-metrics-badges.tsx` file for fine tuning the `WorkspaceCard`. I've made changes to the component to make sure the container stacks on smaller screens (`xs:`) but lays out horizontally on larger screens. I realized that Tailwind doesn't have an `xs:` breakpoint, so I'm leveraging `sm:` for the horizontal layout change, which is working better than expected.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
